    <briefdescription>
<para>The <ref refid="structhaldls_1_1vx_1_1_common_neuron_backend_config_1_1_clock_scale" kindref="compound">ClockScale</ref> determines the range of the clock and at its precision It&apos;s an exponential power-of-two clock scaling factor: For a given reference clock of f_clk = 250MHz, the resulting frequency is f_clk / (2 ^ (clock_scale + 1)). </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>This enables clock frequencies from 125MHz (clock_scale = 0) to ~4kHz (clock_scale = 15) See documentation and implementation of RefractoryTime for more background information. </para>
    </detaileddescription>
